description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week, office hrs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Following the merger of Cumbria Partnership NHS Foundation Trust and North Cumbria University Hospitals Trust, we currently have opportunities for HR Advisors to join our team, on a permanent basis. We are a strong team of HR Business Partners and HR Advisors supporting a large, complex and unionised workforce.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Acting as the first point of contact, you will be providing responsive and proactive advice to managers and staff.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be responsible for managing your own caseload of work including sickness absence, disciplinary, grievance, performance capability, organisational change and HR project work. You will also be responsible for arranging and supporting formal hearings and supporting at any investigatory meetings.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have a special interest as part of your role, covering for example, workforce planning, learning &amp; development, recruitment &amp; retention, organisational design, or occupational health. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In addition, you will contribute to the development of policies and procedures and will also deliver our “People Management Programme.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be flexible and work in close liaison with other members of the HR Department in order to ensure continuity of the whole HR Service across the Trust. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to demonstrate good interpersonal skills and the ability to gain credibility to build effective relationships with managers at all levels within the organisation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Organisational skills, and a good knowledge of employment law is essential for this role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have a Degree in Human Resources or HR Knowledge acquired through relevant training and experience working in an HR environment to degree equivalent level. You must have an ability to work on your own initiative whilst working to tight deadlines, and coaching, motivational and negotiating skills are essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There will be a need to travel across North Cumbria to provide support to other sites but the role will primarily be located at Carlisle.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Should you have any questions on these vacancies please contact Angela Hodgkison, HR Business Partner via email angela.hodgkison@ncic.nhs.uk or 07813 997646.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please ensure that you document evidence of meeting all the essential criteria in the supporting information.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;If sufficient response is received this post could be closed earlier than the specified closing date, please apply as soon as possible to ensure that your application is considered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust is committed to safeguarding adults and children therefore if the post is subject to the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act (ROA) 1974 (Exceptions) Order 1975 (as amended) the successful candidate(s) will be subject to a criminal records check with the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS). The cost of the DBS must be met by the successful candidate(s) through salary deduction. DBS charges are as follows &lt;strong&gt;if applicable to the post:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Standard Check: £26 + Administration cost of £4.20 = deducted at £10.20 from 1st month salary and £10 deducted from salary over following 2 months.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Enhanced Check: £44 + administration cost of £4.20 = £15.20 deducted from 1st month salary and £11 deducted from salary over following 3 months.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of the one of the largest employers in the UK NCIC future employees will have also access to the following benefits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A lease car may be available for this position; further details will be provided upon appointment if applicable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;27 day holiday scheme rising to 33 after 10 years &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Flexible working Scheme &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent opportunities for development &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Competitive NHS Pension scheme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Access to NHS discounts with retailers and leisure companies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;EAP (Employee Assistance Programme) a free, confidential counselling and information service to assist with personal or work-related problems&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;These schemes are subject to availability&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
